text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied. 
in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied. 
in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the effos made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to cou documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the cou documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
notícias e esclarecimentos da postagem anterior : henry cavill diz que não flerta por medo de ser acusado de assédio 'é assim: eu não quero ir falar com uma mulher, porque serei chamado de estuprador ou algo assim', falou o ator em entrevista a revista australiana."as coisas têm de mudar, absolutamente. "há algo de maravilhoso em um homem indo atrás de uma mulher. eu acho que uma mulher deveria ser cortejada e perseguida, mas acho que eu sou tradicional por pensar assim", disse.
"é muito difícil fazer isso se há certas regras no lugar. porque é assim: 'bem, eu não quero levantar e ir falar com ela, porque eu serei chamado de estuprador ou algo assim'. então você fica, tipo: 'esquece, eu vou chamar uma ex-namorada, e depois voltar para um relacionamento que nunca funcionou de verdade'. mas é mais seguro do que eu me jogar nas chamas de um incêndio, porque eu sou alguém que está sendo observado pelo público, e se eu flertar com alguém, quem sabe o que pode acontecer?", falou.
"agora você não pode tentar persuadir alguém que disse 'não'. é tipo: 'ok, tá bom'. mas depois é: 'ah, por que você desistiu?', e eu penso: 'bem, porque eu não queria ir pra cadeia?", concluiu.
o posicionamento do ator gerou muitas críticas nas redes sociais. após as críticas, cavill soltou um comunicado de esclarecimento por meio de sua agente: "vendo a reação a artigo, em particular sobre meus sentimentos em flertar e sobre o movimento #metoo , eu quero me desculpar por qualquer confusão e má interpretação que isso criou. ser insensível não era a minha intenção".
"eu quero esclarecer e confirmar que eu sempre mantive e sempre manterei o máximo respeito pelas mulheres, não importa se a relação for de amizade, profissional ou romântica. nunca quis desrespeitar ninguém de maneira alguma. essa experiência me ensinou uma valiosa lição sobre contexto e liberdades editoriais", finalizou. fonte (  https://www.google.com/amp/s/emais.estadao.com.br/noticias/gente,henry-cavill-diz-que-nao-flerta-por-medo-de-ser-acusado-de-assedio,70002400089.amp ) observação: no site de origem tem o que as pessoas falaram sobre a declaração do henry

text:
10:30am in anchorage, alaska and a tangerine pink powder puff sunrise suspended moment is not to be missed! but, it happens. everyday, we turn. the sun appears to rise and we are (briefly) illuminated. it’s in those moments of transition where the most fleeting, spectacular, sensational, jaw dropping, conversation stopping dance of light and dark and color and shape and emotion often arise! 
how can we translate the beauty and grace of our planet’s pirouette into the rhythms of our own life?
can we pause and gaze with gratitude at the beauty before us? what transitions are unfolding before you? 
has someone just arrived or left? are you breaking up? getting together? starting something? finishing up? is it messy? are you a bit unsure? 
we all are. 
take refuge in your own loving heart, help it grow stronger and more accessible by listening closely to its call, by putting yourself in the presence of kind and generous people, by letting yourself love whatever it is that you do. even if, especially when, it’s not the easy thing to do. sometimes it’s saying no to the celebration so you can stay home and pet your dog... and weep. 
may you know the beauty that you are. may you be guided by grace and may all of the colors appear in your rainbow...
wishing you, wishing always, for peace and so grateful for joy!! may 2019 carry us with care. 
resolved? me too. 
i’m offering a little intro to meditation series in anchorage before our winter retreat. wednesday, 1/2, 5:30-6pm. check calendar (link to website in bio) for more details or dm me! 
thank you for your practice - and delight in all of the ways that it appears! 🙏🏼 #resolved #2019 #solsticelight #winter #alaska #anchorage #yogateacher #meditation #meditationteacher #alaskayoga #sunrise #practice #thisisyoga #metoo

text:
in 2018, i saw folks show up, stand up, speak up, build community, bring courage, find compassion, get taken to the edge, fall down, fuck up, find intention, fight like hell, and face opposition with radical joy and fierce determination.
•
the photos in this collage were generated by #2018bestnine, but of course, they only encapsulate a fraction of the work. there are so many everyday heroes, organizers, and supporters doing the work that doesn’t get publicized or amplified. they’ve been doing it for years, decades, and generations, and will continue to do it despite who’s in office. it’s lifework. 2019 is here — let’s keep going and raising each other up. 🙌🏽

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided repos about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election. - one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
"faz pouco tempo que corro, mas desde a adolescência, faço caminhadas ao ar livre. minha cidade é pequena e relativamente segura. mas, quando estava caminhando em uma avenida, um cara estacionou do meu lado, abriu a porta do carro do passageiro e me mandou entrar. nunca senti tanto medo na vida! em uma outra ocasião, eu estava caminhando com minha irmã em uma avenida e um cara passou de carro por nós duas vezes. na segunda vez que ele passou, minha irmã só disse pra mim “corre”. começamos a correr, entramos num mercado e aí ela me explicou que ele estava olhando para nós e se masturbando 😱 agora que eu corro na rua, sinto muito calor e não penso duas vezes em arrancar a camiseta e ficar de shorts e top. mas mesmo colocando o fone de ouvido no talo para evitar ouvir merda, às vezes a gente vê a forma como eles nos olham... é assustador, repugnante. às vezes consigo ouvir as cantadas idiotas, mas só o olhar já basta para eu sentir repulsa, medo, insegurança!!!" ✊🧡
.
relato da fabiana barbosa, 27 anos, indaiatuba/sp
.

text:
"may we never meat again"
the hindu businessline, 28.12.18
by anita roy:
"looking back at 2018, it seems like this year has been a tipping point of sorts. not so much #metoo but #meat?oo! "vegans have come out of the woods, and staked a claim to the mainstream. "supermarket shelves are stocked with vegan products — some now have whole aisles dedicated to plant-based, meat-free, dairy-free, cruelty-free products. they’re not free — but, as with organic foods, the slow and steady upsurge in popularity for vegan products is beginning to bring prices down. "what has driven this turn away from meat? the headline for the guardian’s environment editor damian carrington’s article published in may sums it up in a nutshell: “avoiding meat and dairy is the ‘single biggest way’ to reduce your impact on earth.” "he references a study published in the journal science and co-authored by oxford academician joseph poore, which begins with a stark fact: “with current diets and production practices, feeding 7.6 billion people is degrading terrestrial and aquatic ecosystems, depleting water resources, and driving climate change.” "if that wasn’t enough to put you off your tandoori chicken, there are also the rising fears of what pesticides and chemical fertilisers, not to mention gm crops, are doing to our food, as well as the additional horror of how plastics have now entered the food chain and are ending up clogging our internal systems just as much as our external ones. "there’s also an increasing reluctance to see fellow sentient beings — cows, pigs, chickens, mainly — as simply ‘raw material’ fed into one end of the agro-industry and squirted out at the other on to our dinner plates."
https://www.thehindubusinessline.com/blink/cover/veganism-may-we-never-meat-again/article25850554.ece
#govegan
#meateww
#veganuary2019
#veganuary

text:
happy new year! 2019 marks our fifth anniversary and as such, we are very excited to announce a special aulos tour coming this spring!

we are presenting expanded and updated versions of two of our previous critically-acclaimed productions: 
antigone na h’éireann
and 
women of the mourning fields

as a double-bill this march!

we'll be bringing the shows to: 
summerhall, edinburgh (28th-30th march)
scottish youth theatre, glasgow (24th march)
and the rondo theatre, bath (9th march)

stay tuned for more tour dates/location announcements in future!

in the wake of the 2017 #metoo movement and the 2016 referendum, aulos returns with two powerful plays, both timelier than ever before, culminating in a performance on brexit day itself.

you can find all the details about both shows and casts for the revival, as well as ticket links, here on our website:

https://aulosproductions.com/double-bill-tour-antigone-na-heireann-women-of-the-mourning-fields-2019/

#edinburgh #bath #glasgow #theatre #tour #wmf #antigonenaheireann #antigone #antigonenireland #northernireland

wmf publicity credit: aliza hoover at ummatiddle 
antigone na h'éireann publicity credit: eleonore dambre

text:
beethoven sonata 30, opus 109 no. 1
—
by the time beethoven composed this work, his output had declined substantially, perhaps owing to his deafness and disappointments in life. the only complete works to emerge from the period of 1820-1823 were the last three piano sonatas, the missa solemnis and the ninth symphony. even when compared to these imposing works, the e major piano sonata retains its status of a masterpiece. it is a remarkable work in several respects. ·
the first movement has a nearly unique structure: it opens with theme marked vivace ma non troppo that almost immediately slows to an adagio espressivo. thereafter, the two contrasting tempos and utterances alternate. scarlatti and mozart had used such a scheme before, but never in such a bold and innovative fashion. on the surface, this short movement has a serene, almost angelic quality, but, like many other works written during this period, the composition's surface is merely one dimension among many. indeed, nothing about this sonata is one-dimensional. thus, for example, the subdued, brightly lit realm suggested by the beginning of the works eventually leads the listener to sections where the narrative slows down, conjuring up dark shadows that intimate feelings of longing and doubt.
.
.
.
.

text:
le mouvement #metoo  fut initialememt crée en 2006 par l'activiste tarana burke dans le but de soutenir des femmes issues de minorités qui étaient, victimes de harcelement sexuel. depuis lors, le mouvememt s'est étendu aux quatres coins de la planète. l'objectif est aujourd'hui de donner une voix à  toute  personne (homme ou femme) victime de harcèlement sexuel. le mouvement met une emphase particulière sur la lutte contre le harcèlement sur le lieu de travail.le mouvement a pris une ampleur considérable depuis octobre 2017, avec le soutient de personalités tel que alyssa milano et la médiatisation de cas de harcèlememt  tel que l'affaire weinstein. depuis lors, nous remarquons une vague de dénonciations tant bien dans le monde du showbizz que sur la scène politique ou même religieuse. ce mouvement constitue une véritable révolutions car il permet au victimes d'abus sexuels de sortir de leur silence et de réclamer justice.

text: 2018 was not my best year 🙄 until it kind of was "if you want to survive when your life is a raging dumpster fire of grief and pain past and present and it’s all falling down around your feet you need to really, really love yourself. radical, unflinchingly honest, even when you’re desperate and pathetic and you hate everything self love. as mark darcy would say “just as you are.” now, this did not come naturally to me. it’s been achieved through a multifaceted approach i’ve patched together for myself and i’ll share a few tips with you now about how i did it." read more on the blog today 💖 link in bio #mentalhealth #grief #grieving #metoo #survivor

text:
from 11/08 to december 2010 i was in inpatient treatment for the childhood trauma i went through. sometimes i forget what it was all like. sometimes i forget that i was abused at the hands of one of the people i fully trusted, someone who was supposed to be helping me. 
my 6th program. 
three 5150’s, 
19 fucking weeks in a full on wilderness program where i was sexually assaulted and then accused of rape by the same person. no investigation was ever done. i was a problem. a sexual deviant who couldn’t be helped.  and after they sucked as much money out of my family as they possibly could, they told me i was nowhere near ready to go home and told my parents i needed to go to a boarding school. 
i was then sent to a therapeutic boarding school where i was victimized an innumerable number of times by a disgusting man who groomed me for months till i trusted him more than my parents, and then used it all against me for his sexual gain. i wanted any way out, and i ended up in the hospital after i fully tore open a surgical incision from a routine hernia repair i was recovering from. i couldn’t take the abuse any longer, i was in the hospital when i finally confided in my mother about what was happening to me everyday. the individual was arrested the next day. and before i knew it i was on my way to another program. i was 15 years old, and i had given up completely. i was tired. i felt like i had no way out. and once again i was put another program. 
i was fully checked out before i had even been checked in. 
my therapist and many others went out of their way to save me from myself. someone got through to me. something finally clicked. i started opening up. i started working the program. re-engaging in my life. they helped me more than i could ever repay. they handed the life i had given up on back to me.  i just found my personalized yearbook that was made for me right before i went home. i sat and cried for a good hour staring at these photos. remembering everything i’ve survived, and how strong i know i am. it’s time to dust myself off and keep on trucking. i can’t beat myself up over things i never had control over. 💕 
it’s time to be my own hero! 🦸‍♀️ #metoo
name: 👑King Kyleigh👑 (Kyleigh Potts)

text:
discussion / feminity

i feel like as a man, for a long time in my life i did not realized the inequality that face women. inequalities and issues such as double standard, salary gap, rape culture, slut shaming.. i was never scared of walking at night. i never looked behind me to verify if i was being followed. i was never scared of being kidnapped and sold as a sex slave or an escort in the other coast of the country. i was never scared of some kind of "revenge porn" happening to me.

people that i know were actually victims of situation like those. kidnapping. drugging. rape. leaked nudes. groping in public places. its something real and then people are talking about an "already achieved equality of the sexes". dont you let them fool you. where i come from we still judge a girl by the tightness of her skirt and by what she decides to show on her ig account.

i find social medias are not helping that situation where theres hyper sexualization of women. too much pictures that portray women as what seems of a sexual object, an item, a crude article. how can it help women's situation if it places them as individuals good for nothing but taking ass pics? those disproportionate bodies, exaggerated lips, impossible hips sre quickly becoming the "norm", standard silhouettes.

women are more than bodies. women are more than ig models. women shouldnt be scared of walking at night and be the victims of constant fear of men. they shouldnt have old men politicians deciding laws for their bodies. they should decide for themselves. they are your moms. your daughters. your wives. cherish them.

text:
on the 31st of december on new year’s eve, when most were out celebrating the new year or getting ready to, over 100 members of the muslim community, young and old, of central london attended the annual qiyam at a local masjid.

the first speaker addressed the difficult questions muslims have to face on a daily basis. the speaker addressed two such questions, ‘women in islam oppressed?’ and ‘fitting in’. the speaker addressed both in showing we have nothing to hide or be shameful about and rather we should show how women in the west are treated and put the onus back on them (#metoo). the speaker touched on how muslims should be proud of islam and being muslims and never feel the need to fit in and dilute their values and beliefs. the speaker ended with an inspirational reminder from the life of the companion of the prophet muhammad (saw), al-tufayl ibn amr al-dawsi (ra), and how he did not listen to the propaganda against islam rather he thought for himself and became a dawah carrier.

the second speaker spoke to the many youth at the event reminding them of the challenging times they live in. the speaker went in detail about the eminent companion and cousin of the prophet muhammad (saw) jafar ibn abi talib (ra). relating his life and especially his time in abyssinia where he (ra) used his wisdom and foresight to give dawah in the highest court of the najashi king, never compromising his stance but using wisdom to win any arguments thrown at him (ra) by his foes. the speaker concluded with saying the youth have to learn the arguments and ideas and study islam to go forward like jafar (ra) in giving dawah to muslims and the wider community at large.

the event ended with a lively q&a and with food and interaction.

#islam #confidence #standfornothingfallforanything

⁣
.⁣
⁣

path i want to take, i learned that acceptance it’s the key even though it’s very hard at times, and many more things.⁣
⁣
.⁣
⁣

⁣
.⁣

text:
happy 2019!

as you set your intentions for the new year, i offer up the radical notion of being okay with others not being okay with you. we’ve heard the research about how women who are ambitious or negotiate salaries are unlikable. but the flip side — that only women who are obedient are likable — is a trap. staying small so that others can stay small-minded sucks. i know. i did it for many years. what if, instead, we all got comfortable with ruffling a few feathers, enduring some awkward silences and stares, and speaking our truths? imagine that. 
#leadership #women #speakingout #metoo #timesup #resolutions #2019

text:
one year ago today i launched a web site. i thought it would provide design services. my story was still quietly tucked inside, i saw no use of it other than to keep it hidden. 
now it’s out there, and it is needed, and i am honored to be the person who gets to share it. this year will be a year of travel, meeting amazing people, finding commonality, and honoring all we are and that we carry.
in the place of unknown i’ve found my known. follow along...
#stalkingawarenessmonth #nsam #survivor #publicspeaker #theunknown #homecomingtour #metoo #oneyearanniversary

text:
“elijah was afraid and fled for his life. he went to beersheba, a town in judah, and he left his servant there. then he went on alone into the wilderness, traveling all day. he sat down under a solitary broom tree and prayed that he might die. “i have had enough, lord,” he said. “take my life, for i am no better than my ancestors who have already died.” [1 kings‬ ‭19:3-4‬]
-
-
elijah was a very powerful man of god! he was a prophet and god used him in mighty ways! god allowed elijah to have victory after victory .. win after win.. however, in this passage of scriptures
take notice of how afraid elijah was to be killed by jezebel... to the extent of him praying for god to take his life! [to get the full story please read 1 kings 18 & 19]
-
-
now i highlight these passage of scriptures to point out that elijah during this period of his life.. did not have a very positive attitude about his situation and towards god.. he wanted god to take his life because the “pressure” became too much.. he forget that god was on his side! the bible says if god is for us then who can be against us! [romans 8:31].. elijah allowed his environment / circumstances to dictate his posture towards god, to affect his attitude!
-
-
beloved, i want you to know that in this new year, it’s our attitude that will determine our altitude in christ! [amongst other things of course].. i strongly believe that our attitude in this new year will determine if god can use us... if he can trust us.. we cannot allow our attitude to affect our posture towards god! we must not allow our environment / situations to dictate our attitude but instead let us allow our attitude to dictate our outcome so that we can be more effective for god! #godbless🙏🏽 #happynewyear✨ #jesuslovesyou💛 & #metoo

text:
mgtow 101: principles and accountability

when i debate people i like to focus on the common principle. by common principle i mean the overall answer that stays consistent, if you swap out the subject, verb or noun.

using this scenario as an example, when people say, "if he didn't want the baby, he should have worn a condom", i say, "what if that same man gave you and the baby hiv, as a result of unprotected sex". would you still say, he should have worn a condom, or would you take accountability and see where you fucked up?

the reason why they make this statement is because the child is a reward and not a punishment to most women. they don't view the baby as directly having a negative effect on their quality of life.

they get money, child support, section 8, food stamps, validation as a mother (by society). they also get the right to always be a victim (blaming the father) as well as unconditional love. if it  weren't for kids, many women would never feel true love, since they don't deserve based off their own merit.

the child benefits her with no consequences. the man has the burden and consequences looming over his head, from the moment she says my period is late.

when you throw the hiv scenario into it, it changes the whole game, she won't get love from others, she can't play the victim about how she got it and she won't get rewarded for having hiv. so she is forced to take accountability. the hiv and the baby stem from the same action, unprotected sex. the lack or principles and accountability is the reason why black women lead in std's as well as out of wedlock births.

the principal stays the same regardless of if you are benefitting or not. if your response or answer changes up depending on if you benefit or not, it shows you lack accountability, character and morals. true accountability is to put the blame on your self in every situation, no matter the factors. women that use this statement without acknowledging she chose the man is a basica.

if she should have worn a condom for the hiv she should also make him wear one to prevent the baby.

what could you have done to make the situation better?

what could you have done to prevent this situation?

text:
2018 to me was the year of transformation, healing and courage.💪🏽🤰🏽🤱🏻🧞‍♀️
when i reflect on the year, i want to point out my gratitude in these moments. .
i am blessed to:
💙have experienced the journey of becoming a mother. the pregnancy, laboring and birth of my son has given me inner strength that i never thought i would achieve. 💙have spent the last year with a community (my futsal/soccer community) of families who i owe so much to. specifically, the 2009 group i coach that is so special and dear to my heart. although winning a national championship with this group was incredible, i have many more memories with this group that i will never forget.
💙have found the strength to purge toxic relationships in work and my personal life
💙have had the courage to take my career into my own hands, starting new projects and expressing my abilities creatively
💙have had the strength to address past childhood trauma head on in the name of healing through intense therapy
💙have the most incredible partner one could ask for who supports me in every way and makes me a better human
💙be living in the age of the girl! the #metoo movement has not only empowered me to speak up about my past experiences but to also address them and heal from within
💙to have so much love surrounding me, z, and v. our community means everything to us. thank you everyone for the support the past year. 💜lesson of the year➡️to stand up for what you believe in and be true to who you are! 🤜🏽🤛🏿🙌🏽
may we all heal and move forward to be the best humans we can be in 2019! blessings to you and yours!

text:
today is the first day our founder, kat gordon, will be sharing daily observations over at @katch_phrases. follow her there and read today’s post below: 
happy 2019!

as you set your intentions for the new year, i offer up the radical notion of being okay with others not being okay with you. we’ve heard the research about how women who are ambitious or negotiate salaries are unlikable. but the flip side — that only women who are obedient are likable — is a trap. staying small so that others can stay small-minded sucks. i know. i did it for many years. what if, instead, we all got comfortable with ruffling a few feathers, enduring some awkward silences and stares, and speaking our truths? imagine that. 
#leadership #women #speakingout #metoo #timesup #resolutions #2019

text:
¿cuánto más tenemos que soportar el maltrato a la mujer?
la crítica mal intencionada para acabar con ella sea quien sea esa mujer, es simplemente eso: una mujer.
porque no cumple con tus pensamientos ya se le trata de porno o de caliente?
ella es una periodista y ella decide como cualquier otra como desea vestirse, pero tratarla así como en este diario "el español" sobre pasa todos los límites.
si lo escribió una mujer, que lástima que destruya a otra mujer con estos escritos públicos. si fué un hombre, el machismo está servido.
debería excusarse públicamente, porque la cabeza enferma no es de quien se viste como quiera, es de quien escribió esta supuesta "noticia". por esa misma regla de tres, todas las féminas que se pongan una vestimenta similar son pornos y calientes. ¡ya está bien!
este escrito colabora al abuso, violaciones, agresiones y maltrato a las mujeres. 
en un mundo donde luchamos por el no maltrato a la mujer en ninguna de sus formas, esto es una vergüenza! esto se llama maltrato mediático! empezamos mal el año! no se cambia, se incita la violencia hacia la mujer. es indignante e indigno, tratar de acabar así con una persona, porque las mujeres deseamos simplemente ser tratadas como personas. ¿es tan difícil comprenderlo? #crispedroche #antena3 #pedrochecampanadas #elespañol #cristinapedroche

debería excusarse públicamente, porque la cabeza enferma no es de quien se viste como quiera, es de quien escribió esta supuesta "noticia". por esa misma regla de tres, todas las féminas que se pongan una vestimenta similar son pornos y calientes. ¡ya está bien!
este escrito colabora al abuso, violaciones, agresiones y maltrato a las mujeres. 
en un mundo donde luchamos por el no maltrato a la mujer en ninguna de sus formas, esto es una vergüenza! esto se llama maltrato mediático! empezamos mal el año! no se cambia, se incita la violencia hacia la mujer. es indigte e indigno, tratar de acabar así con una persona, porque las mujeres deseamos simplemente ser tratadas como personas. ¿es tan difícil comprenderlo?

text:
an imperious lesson from 2018 :  b a l a n c e 
beauty and the beast. ram and ravan.  failure and success. best and the worst. there are legendary poets and novelists who have pen down their thoughts on balance of life. infact, life itself teaches us this very important virtue. do you know why, because one cannot partake success if he/she hasn’t tasted failure! cannot endure sweetness, if bitterness is yet to be experienced; and that’s the jim-dandy of life. if you can once and for all learn to accept and savour the bad and good experiences equally, you’ll start to actually appreciate how your life is at par excellence. 
this is a post from my very own personal experiences, and believe me if i say that 2018 was by far the best year of my life, i literally mean it! just because if i’ve faced the brutally bad times in the past year (#metoo) so have i experienced the most propitious time (#solotravel) as well. the difference i realise in all the other years that have passed and #2018 is the difference of b a l a n c e. you ought to have the two extreme virtues of life in order to make it stupendously alive ! trust me, it works beyond magic and miraculously!

text:
stepping out of the darkness is a very tough thing to do. when you are in a dark place, it’s hard to see the good in anything, and before you know it you are in a dark downward spiral that feels like it has no end.
for me, this is the year that i am determined to close the door to the darkness. it’s been almost three years since i was raped, since my entire life fell apart, since i have been truly happy. we cannot control the things that happen to us, but we can control what we do to make our lives better. we can control the little things we do each day that bring us one step closer to happiness and healing. 
i wish you all the strength, happiness, and many positive  experiences in the new year ahead!💕 . .  #asurvivornotavictim #newyear #toughtuesday #healing #rapevictims #rapevictimrecovery #metoo #metoomovement #opennewdoors #outofthedarkness #outofthedark #positivevibes #happiness #staypositive #bestwishes

text:
resumen del 2018:
12. childish bambino (por su polémico videoclip de "this is america")
11. el director guillermo del toro acumulando premios por la forma del agua.
10. el físico stephen hawking, fallecido este año.
9. aguante nicaragua 💪💪#nicaragualibre🇳🇮
8. se cancela el #nobel de literartura tras el escándalo de los abusos sexuales. #metoo #amítambién #yotambién
7. #seráley argentina, chile y otros países luchando que el aborto sea seguro y legal. 💚
6. el mundial de fútbol (que ganó francia).
5. freddie mercury (revivido en la película bohemian rhapsody)
4. pese a la llegada al poder de líderes de ultraderecha (bolsonaro en brasil, por ejemplo), en américa latina se han producido importantes avances para la comunidad lgtbiq+: se han elaborado marcos legales y ampliado derechos a minorías sexuales o de género en bolivia y ecuador, en argentina se ha promulgado la ley de identidad de género más avanzada del mundo, se ha permitido el matrimonio entre personas homosexuales en méxico y uruguay...
3. el fallecido guionista y creador de superhéroes de marvel stan lee. "todes necesitamos un héroe y a veces hay que buscarlo en la literatura". #stanlee
2. el premiado director alfonso cuarón.
1. los vengadores y otros héroes de marvel desapareciendo tras un chasquido... final épico.
*
y muchas más cosas: la huelga histórica del #8m, el emmy a #lacasadepapel, la moción de censura a rajoy, la acogida masiva de inmigrantes, rozalén diciendo que las mujeres no queremos estar "malamente"...
*
créditos: @pictoline #felizañonuevo #felizaño #2018 #feliz2019

text: i had a woman tell me this year that she didn’t like me at first and that all she knew about me when we met was that i was “the pretty bitch”. i replied that actually i have had issues with myself for years but i decided that’s dumb and i didn’t want to do it anymore. she said “ yeah but i didn’t know that at first”. going into 2019 my resolution is to continue to love myself completely and openly, to proudly be “the pretty bitch” because you know what? it’s so much better than the alternative of going back to hating myself. in 2019 i will support all women and be the best me i can possibly and love myself even when i’m not #supportwomen #feminism #metoo #newyearsresolution #loveyourself #loveothers #bekind #selfcare #selflove

text:
to conclude the series of #aweekofeypsloveniaswomen, we are embracing the last few categories were females stood up and out in the year 2018!

we are leaving all of you with the last few facts of how inspiring girls were in the last circular year!

today, we are putting out the statistics on media and chairs teams of our events in 2018: - 3 out of 5 editors were female,
- 45% of vice presidents were female,
- 47% of media team members were female,
- 57% of chairpersons were female!

we would like to thank all the ladies who have put their effort and hard work into our national committee in 2018!

we would like to end the series of #aweekofeypsloveniaswomen with the words we opened it with: "a new day is on the horizon, and when that new day finally dawns it will be because of a lot of magnificent women..." and we wish that more of eyp slovenia's members, as well as members of the eyp network would support the #metoo movement! let's #wetoo in 2019 together.

thank you.

que as mãos de deus guiem suas vidas para que vocês tenham paz, harmonia, saúde e alegria.

é tudo que desejo neste ano que está começando.

feliz ano novo! 🎆 🤩😘

text:
dear 2018, 
thank you for teaching me  patience, and profound gratitude, but also - and more importantly- how to stand up for myself, how to ask for what i need, and how to stand my ground. 
thank you for giving me all of these experiences, all of these life lessons, the time for self reflection, and the opportunity to make new friends that will last a lifetime. together, we saw some of the highest highs, and some of the lowest lows. although all of these pictures have to do with my career, 2018 has seen me through huge progress in my personal life as well.  i look forward to putting my head down in 2019 and really making things happen. •

text:
the women’s movement fought to bring hardships of womanhood to light; from suffrage rights to income inequalities, the movement has, and is, continually addressing issues that keep women from living a fully free life. 
however, a divide within the women’s movement, specifically between black and white women, has contributed to the rapid decline of the movement and hindered the effectiveness of a shared collective identity. according to black feminist scholar barbara smith, the black feminist movement focused on reproductive issues, equality in healthcare, the prevention of rape culture and sexual harassment, and other important issues. 
unlike the white feminists, black feminists are actively fighting against structural and institutional racism, as well. .
.
.
equality is for all ! 
if racial equality is not a topic of discussion - 
then there is no women's movement... .
no matter the race, sex, gender, beliefs 
united we stand for something 
divided we fall 4 anything. .
.
why not be a queen in 2019? why not be a black feminist? 
why not re-build trust between white women & black women? 
why not build a sisterhood that transcends the test of time....
.
. 
here's a toast to 2019 - another chance to get things right! 
here's to the year of strong women ...
.
.

text:
my 2018? i traveled to 12 countries (yes, one per month). it started with a breakup that propelled me to run away to rome for the weekend, where i got stranded and met up with another woman who also ran away to rome bc of some guy and we both spent the entire day traveling on 3 different trains to get to switzerland in order to fly back home without having to pay like a regular passenger does. but that's why we have to go through such convoluted steps in order to fly back home - we fly for free.

then i got stranded in portugal over the summer and had to pay $1000 in order to fly back home on time for work so i don't get fired, which in the end didn't matter anyway bc i got fired regardless in december not long after i reported a sexual harassment incident and i broke down crying at the vancouver airport, houston airport, newark airport, london heathrow airport about how evil they are to let a predator keep his job while i lose mine. #metoo is a sham.

but the odd part is i bumped into my ex half an hour after i was told i would be laid off and he is now back in my life (yes, he was the one who broke up with me and caused me to run away to rome in the first place). it came full circle in a way, 2018.

but good riddance! i surround myself with friends who are supportive of my nomadic lifestyle, of traveling and writing. i have the means to do so, and even more so now - i am supplied with an abundance of time starting in 2019. celebrating this day now with mimosa for breakfast (yes, just mimosa) and helping a friend move into her new temporary home. 
last night before the festivities, i went to dinner with friends at a chinese restaurant and we each got a fortune that matched what we were going through in our lives. this is what my fortune read.

2019 - i will stay at home. relax. write. plan a month or two by the italian riviera, the adriatic sea, and the rhine. and heal.

guppy new ear. happy nude leer. happy news steer. hubby new drear. puppy do mirror. bubbly mew dear. aptly new beer.

#ladyofleisure #crazyrichasian #2019 #unemployed #funemployed #newyear #newyearnewyou

then i got stranded in portugal over the summer and had to pay $1000 in order to fly back home on time for work so i do not get fired, which in the end didn't matter anyway bc i got fired regardless in december not long after i reported a sexual harassment incident and i broke down crying at the vancouver airport, houston airport, newark airport, london heathrow airport about how evil they are to let a predator keep his job while i lose mine. #metoo is a sham.

but the odd part is i bumped into my ex half an hour after i was told i would be laid off and he is now back in my life (yes, he was the one who broke up with me and caused me to run away to rome in the first place). it came full circle in a way, 2018.

but good riddance! i surround myself with friends who are supportive of my nomadic lifestyle, of traveling and writing. i have the means to do so, and even more so now - i am supplied with an abundance of time starting in 2019. celebrating this day now with mimosa for breakfast (yes, just mimosa) and helping a friend move into her new temporary home. 
last night before the festivities, i went to dinner with friends at a chinese restaurant and we each got a fortune that matched what we were going through in our lives. this is what my fortune read.

2019 - i will stay at home. relax. write. plan a month or two by the italian riviera, the adriatic sea, and the rhine. and heal.

guppy new ear. happy nude leer. happy news steer. hubby new drear. puppy do mirror. bubbly mew dear. aptly new beer.

text:
the women’s movement fought to bring hardships of womanhood to light; from suffrage rights to income inequalities, the movement has, and is, continually addressing issues that keep women from living a fully free life. 
however, a divide within the women’s movement, specifically between black and white women, has contributed to the rapid decline of the movement and hindered the effectiveness of a shared collective identity. according to black feminist scholar barbara smith, the black feminist movement focused on reproductive issues, equality in healthcare, the prevention of rape culture and sexual harassment, and other important issues. 
unlike the white feminists, black feminists are actively fighting against structural and institutional racism, as well. .
.
.
equality is for all ! 
if racial equality is not a topic of discussion - 
then there is no women's movement... .
no matter the race, sex, gender, beliefs 
united we stand for something 
divided we fall 4 anything. .
.
why not be a queen in 2019? why not be a black feminist? 
why not re-build trust between white women & black women? 
why not build a sisterhood that transcends the test of time....
.
. 
here's a toast to 2019 - another chance to get things right! 
here's to the year of strong women ...
.
.

text:
the women’s movement fought to bring hardships of womanhood to light; from suffrage rights to income inequalities, the movement has, and is, continually addressing issues that keep women from living a fully free life. 
however, a divide within the women’s movement, specifically between black and white women, has contributed to the rapid decline of the movement and hindered the effectiveness of a shared collective identity. according to black feminist scholar barbara smith, the black feminist movement focused on reproductive issues, equality in healthcare, the prevention of rape culture and sexual harassment, and other important issues. 
unlike the white feminists, black feminists are actively fighting against structural and institutional racism, as well. .
.
.
equality is for all ! 
if racial equality is not a topic of discussion - 
then there is no women's movement... .
no matter the race, sex, gender, beliefs 
united we stand for something 
divided we fall 4 anything. .
.
why not be a queen in 2019? why not be a black feminist? 
why not re-build trust between white women & black women? 
why not build a sisterhood that transcends the test of time....
.
. 
here's a toast to 2019 - another chance to get things right! 
here's to the year of strong women ...
.
.

however, a divide within the women’s movement, specifically between black and white women, has contributed to the rapid decline of the movement and hindered the effectiveness of a shared collective identity. according to black feminist scholar barbara smith, the black feminist movement focused on reproductive issues, equality in healthcare, the prevention of rape culture and sexual harassment, and other important issues. 
unlike the white feminists, black feminists are actively fighting against structural and institutional racism, as well. .
.
.
equality is for all ! 
if racial equality is not a topic of discussion - 
then there is no women's movement... .
no matter the race, sex, gender, beliefs 
united we stand for something 
divided we fall 4 anything. .
.
why not be a queen in 2019? why not be a black feminist? 
why not re-build trust between white women & black women? 
why not build a sisterhood that transcends the test of time....
.
. 
here's a toast to 2019 - another chance to get things right! 
here's to the year of strong women ...
.
.

text: here’s to 2019... #metoo #wetoo #earpers #2019
name: Dominique Zietsman
tweet_full: here’s to 2019... #metoo #wetoo #earpers #2019
pre_proc_tweet: here’s to 2019...

text:
365 days.
52 weeks.
1 year.
you passed like a sigh.
in a hush you were gone.

i closed my eyes, it was jan '18.
i open my eyes wide, it's jan, '19.

a year of dreaming about lost dreams,
hoping for lost hope,
laughing about everything,
crying for attention,
dancing without fear,
fighting,
flying high,
broken hearts,
shattered souls,
minced trust,
a void of endless drama
a year of ups and downs

man in a wig divided a nation, built walls,
#metoo cringed us
earth warned us
wars fuelled us
money tumbled us
fools ruled us
drones burnt us
#terror scared us
floods drowned us
disaster shattered us
cow vigilante shamed us
mob lynching shocked us

yet we thrived

we flew beyond sky
sent a car ahead the precipice of time,
into the great beyond

labels didn't break us
enemies welcomed us
#refugees are with us
they're one of us
built homes
built hope

we thrived

we lost legends
said goodbyes to stars
welcomed babies with open arms
honoured artistes
welcomed gays, lesbians
united races

jumping on
swimming into a vortex of disaster
grabbing lifeboat of friends

thinking about that lost days
remembering lost legends

here's to 2019
a year of infinite possibilities
days of laughter
days of joy
days of wisdom
.
'however bad life may seem, when there is life, then there is hope'- sh.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
ada e. yonath (born 22 june 1939) is an israeli crystallographer best known for her pioneering work on the structure of the ribosome.
she is the current director of the helen and milton a. kimmelman center for biomolecular structure and assembly of the weizmann institute of science.
in 2009, she received the nobel prize in chemistry along with venkatraman ramakrishnan and thomas a. steitz for her studies on the structure and function of the ribosome, becoming the first israeli woman to win the nobel prize out of ten israeli nobel laureates,  the first woman from the middle east to win a nobel prize in the sciences, and the first woman in 45 years to win the nobel prize for chemistry.

text:
hi friends! happy new year! we made it 😊

i wanted to start off the new year by reintroducing myself. my name is stevie. i am the founder of we are her, a nonprofit that helps survivors became healed, empowered, and restored through our online community.

her gives survivors a safe place to voice their story. over 50 survivors have shared their story on our blog (weareher.net). and many more have shared their story via instagram.

in october of 2016, i started her. myself and 4 other friends started sharing pieces of our story every week. then more friends contacted me and wanted to share. then all of a sudden, survivors i didn’t know began to contact me. her kept growing and growing.

while my ultimate goal is to not need her anymore, i know that’s not attainable right now. too many survivors have come out of the woodwork to say #metoo.

so i’m going into 2019 with a few more goals:
🔹be more inclusive for male survivors. i had a male survivor tell me we post a lot of memes that bash males. i never want to make a survivor feel excluded. we have 1 male blog contributor out of 50 so i know her can do better here.
🔹use more gender-neutral pronouns. not all of our survivors identify as female and i want to make sure we’re doing a better job here.
🔹including more survivors who are poc. this goal is very near and dear to my heart for several reasons. i’m hispanic on my mom’s side of the family, and i know how underrepresented latinxs and other poc are when it comes to dv and sexual assault. many white women make leading headlines when women of color who endure the same thing never even make the news and it’s not right. i also live in montana where women living on reservations here are severely underrepresented as well. it’s time that changes in 2019 and her’s going to do it’s part in making sure that happens.
🔹i want to do even more webinars and live events that you can all tune into.

so cheers to 2019! 🥂 i’m wishing all of you nothing but strength, peace, and an abundance of joy! sending you all my her love! -stevie 💙💜 #weareher

text:
[the sun sets on 2018 on the gregorian calendar]
this was a year in which much of the unrest i have already went through was amplified and blown up and i was made to live it all over again. 
i felt i was was forced out of highlands university with a rapid combination of ableism and sexual discrimination/misogyny from the teachers and harrassment from a member of the community. in reality, i was liberated. these establishments do not hold safety or power for me.

i was able to identify the abusive patterns i had been through in my life and i tried to save others from that abuse. i learned much of my family and friends were conditional on them being able to abuse me and illicit my resources and have been learning about what it is like to make boundaries. i learned that the mainstream herbal medicine community is in a bad way right now, but i am so honored to have met members of the herbal community that care about herbal medicine, and they care about marginalized people and trauma survivors.

i learned that as a culture and even as a person, i wasn't centering the experience of marginalized people, and that i needed to do that to start building a better world. the thing i am the most thankful for in 2018 are womxn of color and indigenous womxn. i have learned so much from you, and i will continue to do so in the hopes that i can protect you better from the society that my ancestors have built, and that i benefit from, as my solemn duty.

i moved into an unfinished cottage with my love so that we may try to build a food forest farm together! our love has lasted the trial of this year even though it was our first year together and probably the hardest year of my life, we made it and we are looking forward to a magical farm year to share with you!

i have prioritized my self care, i'm building boundaries that no one (not even my family or lover) will disrespect. i got back into my art. i switched my scientific self study qeue into astrology/tarot/self care rituals/ancestral history and farm magic queue and i am building space for a music corner in my house to ensure i can continue to learn to express myself through the frequency of sound!

im evolving in a big way.👇
name: •G• 🦄🧜👽Demigirl/Genderfluid👔♊🦀

det dagas, släktet fram i styrka går!”

text:
reflecting on 2018:
-2018 was a year of great inner personal growth for me. i let myself go a bit from my typical rigid gym / nutrition regime and focused more on what’s really important.
.
i shifted my focus to my relationships with others and my relationship with myself. i’ve had some really bad things happen to me as we all do when we go through life but i just want you to know you’re not alone and the support of family, friends and therapy have helped me immensely over this past year. i’m happy to say i’m not the same person i was in 2017 in 2018. i have grown my self confidence which i’ve been seeking from within myself.
.
in 2017 i cut ties from some toxic people and toxic relationships. it’s amazing how freeing it can be to cut people out of your life that don’t support you or put you down in anyway. please take my advice and if you ever find yourself in a relationship or even a friendship that isn’t supportive of your dreams or vision that you will leave them behind. if you ever need help with this do no hesitate to reach out to me.
.
celebrate your struggles it is because of them that we thrive💕

the answer is, they themself , if they know the technique of self defense.
we all, as responsible citizens, should motivate everyone to learn self defense technique, because who knows maybe next time the victim is known to you.

text:
i love seeing so many positive posts reflecting on 2018, but i also think it’s important to reflect and share when things aren’t as positive. #realtalk 
2016, 2017 & 2018 have all been really tough. many times it felt hopeless, but i’ve also gained so many things. trusting in god’s timing, perseverance, passion, letting go of fears, putting my mental health first & thanks to the #metoo movement, i felt strong enough to share my #metoo story with people close to me. 
i’m not sure what 2019 will hold, but whether it’s high or continues to feel low, i’m ready. thank u, next.

text_retweet:
repost @domzthompson: "you may not like this undercover video or the source of the original video.  however, it’s important to understand what is happening in this video.  it’s also important to understand what some of your tax dollars are being used for.  according to data released in recent years, the number of monkeys used for u.s. biomedical research hit an all-time high.  over 100,000 to be exact. use of animals in labs is very common not only here in the u.s., but worldwide.  it’s important to note that nonhuman primates are not the only animals being used for research.  cats, dogs, rabbits, farmed animals and more are also used in private labs and universities around the world. the rise of testing of animals is because of the reported rise of diseases. it’s also because of the demand for commercial and cosmetic product development. i’m not going to deny some research in science has yielded some results some of us have benefited from however, this way of rd is outdated. there are now modern alternatives available and being proposed in ai technology and more, without the use or need for animals. some of these alternatives include the tissue-on-a-chip model, imaging, microdosing and more. the current traditional way of research and development using animals (it should be renamed to research and no development because no real solutions is happening in modern times) should be removed and replaced with alternatives in technology aforementioned. in summary, this is your tax money at work. i also think it’s important for you all to be aware what is happening with these animals because i would want someone to inform me of the things i did not know of or contributed to.  but hey, maybe that’s just me because i do genuinely care about all animals. i hope you all do too. - dom ✌🏽🌱🐘
.
.
📹: @peta"

text: one year ago today, the @timesupnow legal defense fund was founded in the wake of the #metoo movement. at the time of its creation, it seemed like a long shot to make progress when everyone was either an accuser or an accused. nevertheless, that’s exactly what happened. throughout the country, women testified their accounts of trauma; from a court room in lansing, michigan, to a senate hearing for a supreme court nominee in washington, they spoke up. sexual predators who abused their power were exposed and rightfully ousted. companies were being held accountable for the way they treated sexism in the workplace. women who are under ndas felt comfortable and dauntless enough to break their silence. women were a major force in the 2018 midterms to the point where the house is now under democratic control. cultural arts featuring female characters are passing the bechdel test. as i’m typing this, ronan farrow isn’t the only journalist investigating allegations. all this happened in 365 days. the catch? we’ve only just begun. #timesup 🖤

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied. 
in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied. 
in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
2018 is the one year i am excited to put behind me. i’ve been battling with ptsd, insomnia, severe depression, and anxiety after being sexually assaulted for several months in utah. i convinced myself that everyone had bad intentions to hurt you and that there’s no more love in this world. i felt so trapped in utah, i’d wake up with severe anxiety on the days i’d have to leave my room.
••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
i decided it was time to move back home to rediscover a healthier reality and i’m so glad i did. i learned to love again and that’s including myself. my boyfriend has been nothing but patient and caring to show me that good men do exist. he bought me a german shepherd puppy to be my best friend and my protector and it’s been the most fun journey yet. ••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••••
i’m also forever grateful for our savior. he’s never left my side and has always directed me to where i need to be to be happier. may we always remember the new year as a symbol of hope that christ brings through his atonement and that we don’t have to stay who we were last year. we can better ourselves through christ. happy new year, everyone! ❤️🕊

text:
#2018 i had only had 4 speaking engagements.. its clear to me that this yr wasn’t so much about me helping others but about me helping me. i spent 365 days thinking and writing about my life... it has been one mind blowing journey... as a #writer i was forced to look at my life in ways i had never done before... many days i cried-but i continue to write—- i had straight up melt downs and @lukeburke came to chicago and treated me to a wonderful meal and i went right back to writing. i had sleepless nights, @chloechanel_rlt stayed by my side——i ate like tons of  @morecupcakes  i went to therapy and i pulled my shit together and went right back to writing. 
i learned things that crushed me but each time i picked up the pieces and went right bk to writing. because jesus said to pick up your bed and walk.. ——there was healing in each step i took. 
i learned to have compassion for little rae because them muthafuckers tried to take her out. i leaned to respect rae the woman because some ppl would have never survived her life.... but god’s favor and my fedality was steadfast and unmovable *sips tea* ☕️💋 my heart is filled with gratitude for all that 2018 was and hopeful for everything 2019 will be. happy new year!! 🎊🎈 —————————————————————

text:
.
به تمام نیویورکی‌های ترنس و غیر باینری: ما شما را می بینیم، شما را می شنویم و به شما احترام می گذاریم. از سال 2019 تمام نیویورکی‌ها قادر به تغییر جنسیتی در گواهی تولد خود به m، f یا x خواهند بود - بدون توجه به گواهی پزشک🌈

دو پست قبلی به اندازه‌ای که نیاز بود در زمینه جنس و جنسیت صحبت کردیم اگر سوالی داشتید به اون دو پست مراجعه کنید.

هویت جنسیتی (gender identity): احساس عمیق و درونی یک نفر از جنسیتش؛ برای افراد تراجنسیتی این جنسیت مطابق با جنسی که در بدو تولد به آن‌ها نسبت داده شده نیست. بیش‌تر افراد [به ویژه اگر به دوگانگی جنسیت معتقد باشند] جنسیت مرد یا زن (یا پسر و دختر) دارند. جنسیت برخی افراد به طور دقیق برابر با یکی از این دو انتخاب نیست. بر خلاف بیان جنسیتی (که در پایین توضیح داده شده)، هویت جنسیتی برای دیگران قابل مشاهده نیست.
#ترنس #ترنسجندر #هویت_جنسیتی #trans #lgbt #trsnsgebder #metoo #pridemonth #gaypride #lesbian

text:
there are 12 million college womxn in the us. over 20% will experience assault. yet survivors are often told they are the only one, are made to feel alone, and are actively isolated. victim blaming, lack of transparency, lack of trauma informed resources are just some of the ways colleges and universities foster  isolation. but having disciplinary procedures meant to silence survivors and suppress epidemic level rape culture on campus is another. we have to be revolutionarily honest in talking about who gains from womxn’s silence.

this year, our resolution is community. to create as much of it as possible, for it to be honest vulnerable messy and beautiful. and to make sure, especially for survivors, that no one feels alone. 
because you aren’t the only one.
you didn’t do anything to deserve this. 
and you deserve community that supports and lifts you.
join us.
📸 thenastyhands

text:
new day, new dreams, new hopes..
.
.
definitely 2018 was a memorable year for us, #keralites . we started the year by tackling #nipah , one of the most deadliest virus in history. the whole world vowed before our #determination .
.
the next nightmare came in the form of #rain , which brought the worst #flood ever in 94 years of our state's history. from our sunken state, we rose up like a phoenix. the world saluted to our #brotherhood.
.
we smiled to the world with the blooming #neelakurinji , a once in a 12 years experience..
.
hashtags like #metoo , #sabarimala , #genderequality , #transgender have gone viral, ensuring #equality irrespective of the sex.
.
2018 was definitely a year to cherish as well as an year to learn some life lessons. let's hope 2019 goes all right.. have a happiest new year..
.
.
.
.
.
.
#happynewyear #travelphotography #travelholic #travelblogger #letsrebuildkerala #kerala

text:
"lyssna till ditt hjärta och gör vad det råder dig till" ulf stark, göran och draken.
det ni gillat mest: midsommartal i hällregn, bonnstan, skellefteå, färgstarka möten, rejäla kontraster och utmaningar i kenya, sagolik sommar i arvidsträsk, pollensäsong och massor av resor och läsinspirerande jobb (bl a äskil äter träd, embla-böckerna) samt hemmahuset.
mitt absolut finaste minne från 2018 är när jag fick läsrörelsens unika pris till minne av ulf stark. ofattbart fint och jag blir lika rörd varje gång jag tänker på ulf stark-dagen i stockholm ♥️📚. och ulfs ord: "lyssna till ditt hjärta och gör vad det råder dig till" är sedan länge ledstjärna i mitt liv. 
annars är 2018 präglat av: mod att våga språnget att frilansa, att säga nej, #metoo, försök att göra något åt orättvisor och att hitta vägar för att fortsätta utvecklas. inte lätt alla gånger. men 2019 kommer ge mig bra livsträning. god fortsättning #bestnine2018 #jagminnsmitt2018 #vadenbibliotekariegör #livsträning #ulfstarkpriset #lyssnatillditthjärta

text:
2018... you gave me my first 8weeks of placement as a student nurse, 
you gave me new friends, 
you gave me new jobs and experiences, 
you gave me a holiday to amsterdam and memories i’ll never forget, 
you gave me the lowest lows i’ve ever experienced, 
but most importantly...
you gave me a voice.  a voice to share my experiences, 
a voice to tell my story, 
a voice to open up about my mental health, 
this year i was diagnosed with ptsd following a sexual assault i experienced, 
i’ve realised that no matter how hard you try to avoid a problem the more you push it away the harder it is to deal with, 
i’ve started therapy for my bulimia, 
and i moved back home to get support from my family and take care of both my physical and mental health. 
i am so grateful for the lessons i’ve learnt this year and i’m so proud of how far i’ve come. here’s to 2019, i’m going to be more open to sharing my story, and embrace every challenge thrown my way. bring it on! ▫️▫️▫️▫️▫️▫️▫️▫️▫️▫️▫️▫️▫️▫️▫️▫️
#nye #2018 #metoo #metoomovement #mentalhealth #sexualasault #bulimia #recovery #consent #itsokaynottobeokay #ptsd #ptsdawareness

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the beginning.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are helpless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

trump is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still is that republicans willingly piggybacked this lunacy while campaigning for the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.
